<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Guts" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Guts,</orth> bowels, intestines of the belly: <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.285" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 285</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.285" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 285</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.172" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.172" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 172</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 61</bibl>. &lt;*&gt;roil.  <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 3, 33</bibl>. Used to denote gluttonous or corpulent persons: <cit><quote>thou clay-brained g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.251" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 251</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'll lug the g. into the neighbour room,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.212" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 212</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>